  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel the <strong>butternut squash<span class=\"text-danger\">[es] </span></strong>and cut in half using a sharp knife</p><p>Tip: Be careful! Drizzle the knife with a little vegetable oil for easier chopping</p><p>Scoop out the seeds with a spoon and discard</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1637149787897-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1637149787897-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1637149787897-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1637149787897-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1637149787897-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut narrow slices (about 1cm apart) into the <strong>butternut squash halves</strong>, making sure not to cut all the way down to the base – this is your <strong>hasselback butternut squash</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>ras el hanout</strong> and <strong>dried oregano</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> in a small bowl<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>spiced marinade</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1637149791527-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1637149791527-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1637149791527-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1637149791527-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1637149791527-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>hasselback butternut squash </strong>to a tray and drizzle over the <strong>spiced marinade</strong>, then cover with <strong>tin foil</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 40 min or until the butternut squash is soft</p><p>After 40 min, remove the tin foil and cook for a further 5-10 min or until golden – this is your <strong>spiced hasselback butternut squash</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1637149795614-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1637149795614-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1637149795614-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1637149795614-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1637149795614-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>spinach</strong> to a colander and pour over the <strong>boiled water</strong> so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold</strong> <strong>running water</strong> until cool</p><p>Squeeze the water out of the <strong>cooled</strong> <strong>spinach</strong>, then chop it roughly</p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1637149799228-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1637149799228-x400.jpg",
